title: The Big Move
author: lindsay
text: sitting there in total silence,  surrounded by cardboard boxes.  clearing everything out of my room,  getting ready for our big move.   loading furniture into the truck,  going back for more of my stuff.  saying all of my last good-byes,  trying not to shed tears or cry.   looking back as we pull away,   it was late april or was it may? pulling out of our old street,  hoping there will be new neighbors to meet.   as we pull in to candlebury trail they remove the sign that says for sale we unload or boxes into our new rooms,  knowing we will meet our new neighbors soon.   a few weeks have now past and we have all settled in.  we have now become our old selves again!

title: I Am
author: lindsey
text: i am a girl who likes the outdoors but hates mosquitoes.  i wonder why bug spray doesn't work.  i hear them buzzing by my ears.  i see them banging against my window.  i want them to stop biting and sucking my blood.  i am a girl who likes the outdoors but hates mosquitoes.   i pretend to have imaginary mosquito netting.  i feel them sucking my blood.  i touch my itchy bug bites.  i worry i have not put enough bug spray on.  i cry when i see a stagnant pool of water.  i am a girl who likes the outdoors but hates mosquitoes.   i understand why they bite me.  i say there should be more bug-eating animals.  i dream they will become extinct.  i try to slap them when they land.  i hope i don't catch malaria.  i am a girl who likes the outdoors but hates mosquitoes.

title: Future of Grover Middle School
author: lumeng (jenny)
text: always thinking,  always learning,  always getting ready for the future;  ready to adjust with its surroundings.   new technology,  new responsibilties,  new ideas, hopes and goals; new dreams.   going forward,  going higher,  going into an unpredictable future; changing with what each passing year brings.   black and gold shine on the walls,  intellience, dignity,  and pride.  the quiet buzz of talk that echoes off these very walls,  will soon be replaced by the talk of the future.   the transitions are unstoppable,  fast as the running of a jaguar.  the school mascot that never stands still,   galloping through waves of strength,  courage,   sophistication,  and enthusiasm.   i'm proud of this school,  proud of its accomplishments,  proud that i grew up with it,  and went with it,  into the future of grover middle school; the future of my  school.

title: Milk Chocolate

text: every once and a while,  my poster flies down,  off the wall,  onto the wooden floor.  the tape weakens and it can't help but go soaring and whirling down.  the dog on the poster looks sad,  almost as if he has been disappointment to me,  though he hasn't.  he is nothing but fake,  nothing but surreal.  though he does look fluffy and furry,  cute and cuddly,  wild and wistful,  sweet and sugary.  the dog now has a name,  milk chocolate.  the name describes his face,  though he really is white as snow.  he is sweet like milk chocolate.  milk chocolate is still on my wall,  still standing in the field of flowers where he will remain for a very,  very,  very long time.

title: Talking through my chakras
author: madison
text: heavens bells can ring and seem very faint but they really are just a dimension away.   thatâ’s how i see it all: laid out in beautiful pastures and trees like you could never imagine.  heaven is covered up with a black velvet tunic that transforms into the structures of the elements - fire,  water,  air,  wind,  and earth  heaven can be anywhere  - you just have to look.  not with  your human eyes,  but with your spiritual eyes  many people see heaven when they die but others can see it when they close their eyes.  the colors are my favorite part.  thereâ’s this very unearthly one -  itâ’s a beautiful indigo that symbolizes wisdom and prosperity and you earn this color by being wise beyond your looks,  but i was born with this color - the color of healing.   there's another beautiful color to the spiritual spectrum - it rests upon your head like a angels halo  itâ’s a wide violet shaded flower that stretches through the veins of the earth and it can linger in your heart forever but many people shut it out and lock the doors and windows in their minds.  those people aren't defiant they're just scared about what might happen when they look another direction.  because of this they usually become spiritually blind.  this provokes them to pursue the bad opportunities the ones that give you chills at night.   negative energy can take its toll on these people who are blind and afraid of their destinies  but what makes them different is that their spirituality can't define who they are.  usually the angels still soar around them in disguises of colors painted by humanity so say the grass or the dog next door.  the angels are everywhere pushing and guiding us along.  so many people put themselves in categories: the nice,  caring,  beautiful,  evil,  selfish,  rude.  those categories can't tell them what they are - only they can tell themselves who they are,  - even the criminals who do evil things can still be forgiven and blessed either way the disordered,  the deformed,  the mentally challenged,  can tell you what they see because everyoneâ’s eyes are different and those people have the gifts to see not only the wonders of living on earth but the little things that change our world.  theyâ’re sensitive and intuitive about those changes and thatâ’s what we should look up to - not to our sisters or brothers or even our parents - just look at those people who can see truly everything and smile at them make them feel wanted on this earth show them you care and just smile the purest richest smile and say â“helloâ” as if you were welcoming them to the world.

title: Le Savoir (The Knowing)
author: makenzie
text: darkness creeps in,  from doors,  from windows,  the sky is no longer blue,  hatred and lies have consumed.   a deep mist burns my eyes,  smells of potent tears and  death.  it goes up my nose,  i feel a little dizzy.   i see a distant light,  pure,  golden,  bright.  it's coming closer as if i can reach out and touch it.  where am i?!

title: Greif
author: manda
text: grief the loss has hurt me,  damaged me greatly.  my thoughts of you will never be the same,  iâ’m afraid i will never lose the pain.  all of these emotions are coming at once: sorrow,  depression,  and frustration the thought that i will never see you again…  i know it isnâ’t your fault,  but how could you leave? i have known you for years but i never really got to know you.  now,  that chance of that is gone.   i can remember everything about you,  but all of the memories are now distant.  your face,  your smile,  your laugh.  the clothes you used to wear,  the way you wore your hair.  but,  the only remembrance is now few pictures and these distant memories.   the thing that hurts the most is when i want to tell you something.  everybody says you are listening,  but how do i know for sure? i wish so bad that i knew everything.   well,  not everything but close enough to know exactly why you had to leave.  i think you were the only one who understood me.   and now,  nobody really does.   i think about you all of the time.   i swear you are constantly on my mind,  i dream about you every night.  sometimes i think i can see you in the day light.   sorry for being bold,  but you were too young to die.  especially how you died,  and when you died.   i cry for myself because i miss you,  but i feel selfish.  i should cry for you.  your life was cut short.  and i will live.  by: manda

title: I am poem
author: megan
text: i am a student.  i wonder why teachers give us so much homework.  i hear no homework.  i see a homework assignment.  i want no more homework.  i am a student.   i pretend to get my homework done.  i feel glad when it is acctually done.  i touch the pencil,  then put it down.  i worry that my homework is not going to be done.   i cry when i have too much homework.  i am a student.    i understand when people are angry when we get homework.  i say i understand them too.  i dream that all teachers are not aloud to give out anymore homework.  i try not to think about how much homework i have.  i hope the day is almost over.   i am a student.

title: Snowflakes

title: The Boomslang
author: michael
text: the boomslang is mean and green,  deathly black,  venomous and dangerous,  toxic and lethal.  shiny and glossy,  glistening in the sun slithering and sliding,  speedy and swift.  scaling and ascending,  hanging and swinging from branch to branch.   swimming and gliding through the african waters.  actively observing,  motionless and waiting scenting and detecting,  hiding and stalking its prey.  a small and frail little mouse scavenging for berries in the bushes, quietly chewing at the bark.  the snake noiselessly following,  ready and alert creeping towards it - no hope for the mouse! accelerating and lashing out,  hissing and biting,  coiling and crushing,  poisoned and dead.  digesting and devouring,  finished and full,  relaxed and tired,  sleeping and resting.  curled and coiled,  basking and lying in the sun.  the vicious predator lurking in trees ready to strike its next victim . . .   \\

title: A wonderful dream

text: i breathe is the clear,  blue,  unpolluted air,  as i wonder how great it would be if the whole world was like this.   i see the stream slowly rippling across the rocks,  and i wonder,  why isn't it like this everywhere.   i look around and see birds flying in the sky,  deer roaming around,  and squirrels gathering nuts.  all with no worry of being hurt.  i think about a lot of other places in the world  i see the colorful trees standing tall,  i hear birds chirping happily i see the clear air,  smoke free and the green grass,  trashless  i wake up from this dream and think about how it's a shame that people have to stop this dream from being a realality.
